#--------------------------------------------------------------#
# Author: hepia // HES-SO
# Description: Nexys 4 pMOD audio example design
#--------------------------------------------------------------#

The example design realized the link between an audio input pMOD module (12-bits) and an audio output module (16-bits) :

- The audio input pMOD should be connected to the JC connector. Only the left channel is connected.

- The audio output pMOD should be connected to the JA connector.


The archive is organized as follow:

- doc
  - Audio_in: Audio input pMOD documentation
  - Audio_out: Audio output pMOD documentation

- vivado_prj
  - not_gate : Bit inverter component
  - pMOD_Audio_in : Audio input pMOD component
  - pMOD_Audio_out : Audio output pMOD component
  - test_audio_pmod : Top-Level design
  - upsizer_msb : Component used to connect two vectors of different length

- README: This file

